parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shift lever can cause the vehicle to move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The shift lever fails to shift from drive to park
the vehicle moves unexpectedly
the emergency brake must be engaged to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator fan motor switch can cause electrical shorts, leading to fires, which can result in vehicle damage or injuries.
symptoms: The radiator fan motor switch shorts out
starting fires
the fan motor fails to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stuck ignition key can cause the vehicle to be inoperable, leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The ignition key gets stuck
cannot be removed from the ignition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater vent control switch can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The heater vent control switch is inoperable
the heater vent fails to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Seat Belt and Tailgate Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear seat belts and tailgate can cause injuries or accidents, especially in situations where rear seat occupants need to exit the vehicle quickly.
symptoms: The rear seat belts fail to return or come out
the rear tailgate fails to open
the internal computer is suspected to be the cause of the failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Filler Pipe Corrosion and Leaking
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and leakage of the fuel filler pipe can cause fuel to spill onto the ground, creating a fire hazard and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the fuel filler pipe
fuel spills onto the ground while filling up
corrosion visible on the fuel filler pipe.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Rear Door Latches and Liftgate Actuators
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear door latches and liftgate actuators can cause the doors to malfunction, leading to inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents. The sudden opening of the liftgate while driving can cause the contents of the trunk to spill out onto the road, creating a hazardous situation.
symptoms: The rear doors do not open
the liftgate does not open
the liftgate only opens partially
the liftgate and/or glass top open unexpectedly while driving
the liftgate and/or glass top do not respond to remote or button commands.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the liftgate and glass top can cause inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents. The sudden opening of the liftgate while driving can cause the contents of the trunk to spill out onto the road, creating a hazardous situation.
symptoms: The liftgate and/or glass top do not open
the liftgate and/or glass top only open partially
the liftgate and/or glass top open unexpectedly while driving
the liftgate and/or glass top do not respond to remote or button commands.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning climate control system can cause discomfort, distraction, and potentially lead to accidents due to the sudden and unpredictable changes in temperature and airflow.
symptoms: The windshield fogs over randomly
the heat and AC switches randomly between modes
the temperature settings do not respond as intended
the passenger side AC does not work while the heat does
the AC blows cold air on the driver's side but not on the passenger's side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking gas pedal and unintended acceleration can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The gas pedal sticks even when applying pressure to the brakes
the car lunges forward even when the brakes are applied
the vehicle can be stationary and still lunge forward
the issue occurs in both city and rural areas.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning drainage system can cause water to accumulate on the driver's side floor, leading to slippery pedals, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when braking or accelerating.
symptoms: Water accumulation on the driver's side floor
soaked carpeting under the driver's seat
moisture on the brake and gas pedals
slippery pedals
inability to properly grip the pedals.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially when parking or stopping.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected acceleration
vehicle surging forward
no warning lights or indications before or after the failure
loss of vehicle control.
